<div class="c230_16"> 
<div id="v230.16.1"><span class="H4387 s">Michtam</span><span class="H1732 s"> of David</span><span class="H8104 s">. Preserve</span><span class="H410 s"> me, O God</span><span class="H2620 s">: for in thee do I put my trust</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (Michtam: or, A golden Psalm)</span></div> 
<div id="v230.16.2"><span class="H559 s"><i>O my soul</i>, thou hast said</span><span class="H3068 s"> unto the LORD</span><span class="H136 s">, Thou <i>art</i> my Lord</span><span class="H2896 s">: my goodness</span> <i>extendeth</i> not to thee;</div> 
<div id="v230.16.3"><span class="H6918 s"><i>But</i> to the saints</span><span class="H1992 s"> that</span><span class="H776 s"> <i>are</i> in the earth</span><span class="H117 s">, and <i>to</i> the excellent</span><span class="H2656 s">, in whom <i>is</i> all my delight</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.16.4"><span class="H6094 s">Their sorrows</span><span class="H7235 s"> shall be multiplied</span><span class="H4116 s"> <i>that</i> hasten</span><span class="H312 s"> <i>after</i> another</span><span class="H5262 s"> <i>god</i>: their drink offerings</span><span class="H1818 s"> of blood</span><span class="H5258 s"> will I not offer</span><span class="H1077 s">, nor</span><span class="H5375 s"> take up</span><span class="H8034 s"> their names</span><span class="H8193 s"> into my lips</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (hasten…: or, give gifts to another)</span></div> 
<div id="v230.16.5"><span class="H3068 s">The LORD</span><span class="H4490 s"> <i>is</i> the portion</span><span class="H2506 s"> of mine inheritance</span><span class="H3563 s"> and of my cup</span><span class="H8551 s">: thou maintainest</span><span class="H1486 s"> my lot</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (of mine…: Heb. of my part)</span></div> 
<div id="v230.16.6"><span class="H2256 s">The lines</span><span class="H5307 s"> are fallen</span><span class="H5273 s"> unto me in pleasant</span><span class="H8231 s"> <i>places</i>; yea, I have a goodly</span><span class="H5159 s"> heritage</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.16.7"><span class="H1288 s">I will bless</span><span class="H3068 s"> the LORD</span><span class="H3289 s">, who hath given me counsel</span><span class="H3629 s">: my reins</span><span class="H3256 s"> also instruct</span><span class="H3915 s"> me in the night seasons</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.16.8"><span class="H7737 s">I have set</span><span class="H3068 s"> the LORD</span><span class="H8548 s"> always</span><span class="H3225 s"> before me: because <i>he is</i> at my right hand</span><span class="H4131 s">, I shall not be moved</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.16.9"><span class="H3820 s">Therefore my heart</span><span class="H8055 s"> is glad</span><span class="H3519 s">, and my glory</span><span class="H1523 s"> rejoiceth</span><span class="H1320 s">: my flesh</span><span class="H7931 s"> also shall rest</span><span class="H983 s"> in hope</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (rest…: Heb. dwell confidently)</span></div> 
<div id="v230.16.10"><span class="H5800 s">For thou wilt not leave</span><span class="H5315 s"> my soul</span><span class="H7585 s"> in hell</span><span class="H5414 s">; neither wilt thou suffer</span><span class="H2623 s"> thine Holy One</span><span class="H7200 s"> to see</span><span class="H7845 s"> corruption</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.16.11"><span class="H3045 s">Thou wilt shew</span><span class="H734 s"> me the path</span><span class="H2416 s"> of life</span><span class="H6440 s">: in thy presence</span><span class="H7648 s"> <i>is</i> fulness</span><span class="H8057 s"> of joy</span><span class="H3225 s">; at thy right hand</span><span class="H5273 s"> <i>there are</i> pleasures</span><span class="H5331 s"> for evermore</span>.</div></div> 
